== Garlic Rice ==

Pop a medium #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium-high heat with the @butter{20%g}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the butter has melted, add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and the @water for the rice{300%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Spiced Chicken ==

While the rice cooks, put the @plain flour{2%tbsp} and @north Indian style spice mix{1%tbsp} in a shallow #bowl{}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then mix to combine.

Sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

Add the chicken to the bowl of spiced flour, then toss to ensure an even coating. Repeat for the other breast(s).

Discard any spiced flour left in the bowl.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @?oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a board, cover with #foil{}, and allow to rest while you make the sauce.

Wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop on medium heat.

== Tikka Masala Sauce ==

Once hot, add the @tikka masala paste{75%g} and @tomato puree{30%g} to the pan. Cook, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @sugar{1} and @water for the curry{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Mix in the @creme fraiche{75%g} until combined, then remove from the heat. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Taste the tikka sauce and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice the spiced chicken widthways.

Fluff up the garlic rice with a #fork{} and spoon into your #bowls{}, then top with the tikka sauce and sliced chicken.

Enjoy!